description: Join us at Three Brits for an unforgettable evening of drag, music, and celebration. Doors open at 4 PM and we’re going til late , so come early, stay loud, and get ready for a show that slays. ✨ Xana the legendary Métis Two-Spirit queen, Xana — a fan favourite from Canada’s Drag Race Season 5 and a cast member of the upcoming Slaycation Season 2. Known for high-energy routines, iconic high kicks, and off-stage advocacy and fundraising for disenfranchised communities and Trans health care. ✨ Amy Grindhouse is a Vancouver-based drag artist, stand-up comedian, and DJ who brings camp and chaos to every stage. She champions the belief that drag is for everybody, using performance to challenge norms and celebrate pride. ✨ Cheryl Trade is a Nehiyaw Cree 2S queen from Saskatchewan who turned a Halloween costume into a full-blown drag journey. Crowned Miss Gay Saskatoon, she brings confidence, culture, and charisma to every performance. 'Whether I make them laugh with a joke or whether I'm hair flipping I want people to enjoy themselves and have a good time around me.' ✨ Rose Butch the Original Non-Binary Drag Thing, bringing theatrically-charged, gender-expansive drag to Vancouver stages since 2014. Their playful and theatrically-informed work has brought non-binary visibility to stages across Vancouver and beyond. And keeping the energy high all night long? A live DJ spinning beats before, during, and after the show.
location: 1736 Davie ST, VANCOUVER, BC, V6G1W2, CA

description: Azucar Saturday at Mangos Kitchen Bar is the place for Latin Music in Vancouver. Latin dancing will be the main topic during the night. Guest list is not valid during special events (Halloween, New Years , Long Weekends etc..) 4 Types of Tickets Option 1 (Dinner & Dancing (Groups 10 or more People) 6pm-9pm Our $54 Per Person Dinner (Tropical Fix Menu) includes it all and is perfect for a fun date night, or large birthday, anniversary parties, stagettes or any celebration of life. Includes cover charge for the dancing, Dj and dance lesson ,2 course meal from our Tropical Fix menu. Round of Mangos plane shooters for your guests. 3hours per Reservation. After your group can stay for the party. (Note)After dinner  if you want to keep your table (6) for the night just order a bottle for each party of 6. (Example if your group is 10 people you can keep 2 tables and order 2 bottles or you can keep one table and order 1 bottle) $54 plus tax and gratuities per person. Option 2 ( Dinner & Dancing up to 9 People ) 6pm-9pm You can choose from Our Open Menu. Minimum spending is $54 per person Includes cover charge for the dancing, Dj and dance lesson. Courtesy Round of Mangos plane/boat  shooters for your guests when your table reach the Minimum spending. (E﻿xample  Table of 6 minimum will be $54 multiply by the number of guests) O﻿ption 3 Table Service After 10pm This include VIP entrance and a choice of our bottle service packages $300-600 plus tax and tips. Note : each table is for 6 for each extra person will be extra charge. Example : Your Group is 10 people Choice 1 Table for 10 people will be 2 bottles minimum  ($600)and 2 tables,  No cover Choice 2 one table(6) ($300 minimum)  and 4 covers charge $20 each Option 4 (Dancing Only Tickets) After 9pm Want to dance the night away but don't need a seat? General Admission or Line By-Pass Tickets are available here or at door. These general admission/dancing-only tickets do not include food or seating but do include the 9pm dance lesson!
location: Mangos Kitchen Bar, 1180 Howe St, Vancouver, BC, V6Z 1R2, CA

description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha- Beginner Intermediate
description: Class Description This class is dancers that have completed the Fundamentals course and want to continue to improve their social dancing using the techniques they have learned. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: Limited cabaret seating with dance floor. If you need to sit, come early! Presented by The Brackendale Art Gallery Society, with support from BC Live, BC Arts Council & the province of British Columbia Dawn Pemberton is a vibrant, soulful Canadian vocalist and multiple Juno Award nominee whose powerful voice moves effortlessly from gospel and soul to jazz, funk, and world music. Dawn will perform with her 5 piece band. A staple of the Vancouver music scene, she has toured extensively across Canada and Europe, sharing stages with legends like Bettye LaVette and Kurt Elling.

event_name: SwingSoul Vancouver Dance Is Dance Workshop - Special for Pride Weekend
dance_style: dance, swing, wcs, west coast swing
description: In the spirit of PRIDE Season, we are excited to offer a special inclusive Beginner Bootcamp hosted by Dalynne! This workshop is perfect for exposing your Westie-curious friends to the dance. And if you haven't tried swapping roles, why not try something new, or refresh your favourite dance moves with an Intro to West Coast Swing crash course? West Coast Swing is special in that we do not use traditional male or female roles to dance. In fact, this dance has genderless roles, meaning that anyone can learn how to lead or follow, and many people learn how to do both! Dancing is a way for us to express ourselves, and we encourage everyone to dance in whichever way they prefer! Whether you are dancing as a leader or a follower, you don't need to be amazing in order to enjoy yourself, you just need to learn a few essential skills and the rules of the game to have fun. We'll teach you everything you need to get your groove on to any song, with any partner! Details: August 3 at Dance Vancouver Studio 4:30-6:30 pm Super fun crash course taught by our Swing Literacy instructors 7-8 pm Open WCS class: Get the Funk Out! 8-11 pm WCS dance party - everyone welcome ($15 general admission to the party, workshop attendees attend the party for free!) Register here and tell your friends: https://www.swingliteracy.com/dance-is-dance
source: WCS Lessons, Social Dances, and Conventions – BC Swing Dance ...
location: 1627 W Broadway, Vancouver (at Dance Vancouver Studio),  BC, V6J 1W9, CA

description: Get ready to dance, mingle, and make new friends with fellow sapphics on Thursday August 14. Come join us on the The Rooftop of the Stathcona Hotel for dancing, drag performances, beach pong, bracelet making stations, drinks and good vibes. Doors: 9:00pm Beach Pong Competition: 10:00pm Party ends: 1:00am Pop Up Drag Performance by: Cece Cute and Charming, that's Cece. She's an Indigiqueer sweetie with the name so nice you've gotta say it twice. This flirtatious fireweed left the big lake for the Salish sea a few moons ago. She's performed across the North, the West, her bedroom, your bedroom, and has now returned to lək̓ʷəŋən territory. She's the blossom that'll have you toss 'em 🤑💵🌸 Music by: 👱🏼‍♀️ 🩷 Barbie Aphelion is the sapphic people’s choice DJ of Victoria, with over 15 years behind the decks—including 8 formative years in New York City. From New York Fashion Week to Brooklyn’s iconic Mood Ring, to local haunts like Vicious Poodle for U-Haul and leather dyke nights, her resume is as stacked as her USB. Barbie’s on-stage energy is intoxicating (hey Britney), and her connection with the crowd is something you have to feel to understand. Her sets are high-femme and tell a unique story every time—unapologetically wet, dripping in cvnty vocals, dirty basslines, a genre-blurring blend of house, Top 40, R&B, hyperpop, and whatever her divine intuition tells her to play. After a wildly busy year—including a packed fundraiser at a legendary Montreal strip club with an all-trans cast, raising serious coin for a local trans SW organization—she’s gearing up for a Western Canada Tour. Let your inner diva loose, dance it out, and maybe even find someone to make out with. 👽 🚀 Krista Mac is a queer, enby and feminist performer who loves to throw it back to classic songs throughout their sets. Based on the west coast in Vancouver, B.C., they have opened for artists such as Cobrah, Manilla Luzon, The Funk Hunters, Whitney Day, Netta , and TT The Artist . With a strong love of dance pop, edm and deep house Krista Mac draws inspiration from large-scale festival performances to keep any crowd moving.
location: The Sticky Wicket Bar & Restaurant, 919 Douglas Street, Victoria, BC V8W 2C2

description: All classes are registered on a monthly basis with no partner required.
All classes are registered on a monthly basis with no partner required.
All classes are registered on a monthly basis with no partner required.

Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: A weekly dance movement ceremony—an immersive inner and outer journey that calls you home to your body, breath, and heart. description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: balboa, dance, lindy hop, live music, swing
description: Every Friday evening, we're putting on a dance party! Total beginners are always welcome; our drop-in beginner lesson will have you dancing in no time. Neither partner nor experience are required, but pack a spare sense of humour! Following the lesson, the dance features fantastic live music perfect for dancing the night away whether you’re mad about lindy hop, charleston, balboa, or collegiate shag. We've got a regular rotation of bands each month – you can see who is playing each week on our calendar.
location: Dance Victoria, 2780 Quadra St,  BC, V8T 4E7, CA

Following the lesson, the dance features fantastic live music perfect for dancing the night away whether you’re mad about lindy hop, charleston, balboa, or collegiate shag. We've got a regular rotation of bands each month – you can see who is playing each week on our calendar.
location: 2750 Quadra ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8T4E8, CA

description: This is a District of Squamish Recreation Course $78.00 + GST per person. $17.00 + GST per person Drop in. Location: The 55 Activity Centre Squamish Swing Dancing for Beginners and up. We will be introducing the basics to West Coast Swing and one other swing dance. This a great course to have fun, meet people, learn steps and gain confidence to start dancing to the music you love. With 28 years of experience, you are guaranteed to have a good time. Dances being taught: West Coast Swing & Jive 6 weeks = 6 Classes Enjoy the dancing. Call Brennan Park at 604.898.6896 or register online: Activity Start Page (perfectmind.com)

description: Dive into the rhythm this upcoming Friday July 11th at Method Studio (841 Fisgard St) for a night of music, dancing, and fun! We’re taking you Under the Sea Dress in shades of blue, green, sparkly and pearls. Schedule: 8:00 PM – Doors open 8:15 PM – All Levels Bachata Lesson 9:00 PM - 12:00 AM – Social Dance This Friday @sebastianyhannah will teach an amazing open level bachata class! Don’t miss it Dance to the perfect 3:1 mix of Bachata & Salsa!
location: Method Studio, 841 Fisgard St, BC, V8W 1R9, CA

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Bachata Temptation, Salsa Sensation
description: Join us for a vibrant late afternoon of Latin dancing by the ocean! We’ll begin with a beginner-friendly lesson— no partner or experience needed. After the class, enjoy an open-air social featuring a dynamic blend of Salsa, Bachata, and Kizomba, with just a light touch of Merengue to round out the evening. This is a beautiful, inclusive, and supportive community where new friendships are made and everyone belongs.
location: Songhees Plaza (near the Johnson Street Bridge), Songhees Walkway, 1100 Admirals Road, Victoria, BC, V9A 2P6, CA
price: $5 for students (with valid ID), $10 general admission

description: Bachata 4-Week Series. Class: 9PM–10PM | Doors open 8:50pm. Optional Practice: 10PM–10:30PM (Only for students). Perfect for beginners who know the basics and improver dancers wanting to grow their dance and strengthen their fundamentals and flow. Register now: sebastianyhannah@gmail.com. Payment can be done through etransfer at the email or CASH at the day of class.
location: Solwood Studio, 1303 Broad Street, Victoria, BC, V8W 2A8, CA

description: Get ready for a magical summer night filled with Latin rhythms, sunset vibes, and non-stop dancing! Join us for the Salsa Sunset Latin Party, where the Salsa, Bachata, and Merengue beats will keep you moving all night long under the stunning sunset sky! Dress Code: Wear your best sunset-inspired outfit – think bright, tropical colors, and beach party vibes! Dance to the best Salsa, Bachata, Merengue & Latin hits all night! No partner? No problem! Join our fun intro class at 8:00 PM!
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St., Victoria, BC, V8Z 3K9, CA

description: Sunday Swing at Logan's is BACK! Come join us for some great tunes and we'll party like it's 1939. Bring your dancing shoes, sweet moves, and a few dollars for our fabulous DJ (and gracious bartenders). Feel free to come early to hang out and grab a bite to eat. 19+. NEW: Crash course 15min swing lesson at 8:30pm! This is intended to be the bare minimum for someone to show up and know the basics of swing dancing, nothing fancy! DETAILS: * 8:30pm Quickie 15min beginner lesson! * 8:45pm social dancing until as late as midnight (maybe!) * Usually gets bluesy after 11pm.
location: Logan's Pub, 1821 Cook Street, Victoria, BC V8T 3P5

dance_style: dance, swing, wcs, west coast swing
description: Come join us every Saturday all year long for a fabulous WCS social dance from 8 - 11pm. Just $10 for the ($5 for students). Meaghan Efford and Bob Gebbie 's lesson on June 1st (starting PROMPTLY at 7pm) will be the only lesson in June, and it will be a great way to build, refresh or accelerate your skills in the dance, so please be sure to take advantage of this opportunity.  The lesson is included in the dance entrance price.  No experience or partner is required.
location: BC Swing Dance Club Victoria

event_name: West Coast Swing in the Park!
description: Come join us for another evening of fun and WCS dancing in Beacon Hill Park! WCS music will be provided by DJ Carolyn. For those who are familiar with the routine, the 2018 WCS Rally Song will be played at 6:30, 7:30 and 8:30pm. Sam Jackson and Meaghan Efford, from wcsmovementmethods.com will be on hand to answer questions about WCS or how to improve your WCS dancing. They will also demo some incredible WCS dancing at 7pm.
source: West Coast Swing in the Park!
location: Cameron Bandshell, 250 Bridge Way, Victoria, BC V8V 2P2

description: Join us at Solwood Studio in Victoria for a night of dancing, chit chat, and treats. DJ Lama and Nay are visiting from Vancouver, and Grazyna will lead a Chacarera. Dress code: Smart casual. Admission: $15 (cash only).
location: Solwood Studio, 1303 Broad Street, Victoria, BC, V8W 2A8, CA

description: 10 years of Alive Tango in Victoria! 10 years of friendships, events and exploring the music, the movement, the possibilities. 10 years of mutual support in tango and life. So many people came and moved on  but everyone left something behind, built a small piece of Alive. So many of you came but stayed building, creating and shaping us. It takes a village and we all are part of it!!! Afternoon Anniversary Milonga ! Cake (made by Danusia!!)and bubbly ( we encourage you to bring your own water bottle or a cup .. we might run out of the ones in the studio ). Let us know if you can come 12pm-5pm $10 Two amazing DJs : Carol Horowitz ( Montreal) and Dan Boccia ( Anchorage) ( the artwork by Rasanga Weerasinghe)
location: Alive Tango Victoria, 1303 Broad St., Victoria

description: This 6 weeks session is progressive and requires preregistration (no drop ins) and is designed for students who have no experience with Argentinian tango or forgot everything they learned 10 years ago. The course is designed to introduce both roles to each participant (lead and follow) as a way to discover this extraordinary dance. On Wednesdays: August 20th - September 24th.
location: Solwood Studio, 1303 Broad Street, Victoria, BC, V8W 2A8, CA
